Configuracion de VsCode

Configuración de PATH con oh-my-zsh

For MacOS, search for VSCode application for e.g. it was in my Downloads section.
Now copy that to Applications folder and then run following commands.
	•	Open terminal and type vi ~/.zshrc
	•	Add this line in the end (If not empty) export PATH="$PATH:/Applications/Visual Studio Code.app/Contents/Resources/app/bin"
	•	Press command+Q (in short quit the terminal)
	•	Again open up terminal and go to git code folders
You are all sorted now. Thanks

https://stackoverflow.com/questions/29955500/code-not-working-in-command-line-for-visual-studio-code-on-osx-mac


Configuración de Terminal .- Quita el nombre del equipo y el usuario

Solo necesito modificar~/.zshrc

	•	Ocultar nombre de usuario y nombre de host:
prompt_context() {}

	•	Conserve solo el nombre de usuario, oculte el nombre de host:  prompt_context() {if [[ "$USER" != "$DEFAULT_USER" || -n "$SSH_CLIENT" ]]; then prompt_segment black default "%(!.%{%F{yellow}%}.)$USER" fi} 
https://programmerclick.com/article/62711329525/



